
String is a data type in Python
A string is a sequence of characters enclosed in quotes
We can write a string in 3 ways:
    name = "Fethi"      # Double quote
    name = 'Fethi'      # single quote 
    name = '''Fethi'''  # triple quote 

STRING SLICING:
           A String in  Python can be sliced to get parts of a string
              String is immutable  # you cannot change your string (Particular character)

 F  E  T  H  I
 0  1  2  3  4
-5 -4 -3 -2 -1

name = "Fethi"

nameshort = name[0:3] # start from index 0 all the way till 3 (excluding 3)

print(nameshort)

output:
     Fet

